programme.title: Jazz à Vienne
programme.desc: A number of spellbinding performances from Jazz à Vienne, a well-known Jazz Festival that takes place annually, in France. Every evening there are concerts in the ancient Roman theater of Vienne. Among the performers there have been musicians such as Miles Davis, Stan Getz, Michel Petrucciani, Ella Fitzgerald, and many more. In addition to the main concerts there are smaller ones on other stages in the city, and in pubs and musical moves.

programme.title: Portrait
programme.desc: These portraits of artists, concerts and festivals provide a good picture of the jazz world. They are portraits of well-known and less known jazz artists who give us an insight into their lives amongst other things, DJAZZ asked them why they wrote that particular song, what was the first record this musician bought and what his or her most cherished musical memory is. The festival portraits are beautiful reports of the most special jazz festivals and concerts. They revive the festival with the music and experience.

programme.title: I Wouldnt Give a Cripple Crab a Crutch
programme.desc: This selection of unforgettable performances by some of the most iconic and influential male jazz and pop vocalists in history showcases these legends unique essence. Delight in the expressive beauty and emotional depth of Chet Bakers rendition of "Time After Time" and "You Dont Know What Love Is", recorded live in Brussels, Belgium in 1964 and in Rome, Italy in 1956 respectively. Revel in Frank Sinatras iconic version of "Ive Got You Under My Skin". Immerse yourself in Dizzy Gillespies dynamic performance of "Let Me Outta Here", recorded live in Denmark in 1970. Enjoy Tony Bennetts unforgettable performance of "It Dont Mean A Thing (If It Aint Got That Swing)" at Londons majestic Royal Albert Hall in 1974. Let the haunting beauty of Nat King Coles 1957 performance of "Autumn Leaves" and Louis Armstrongs performance of "Basin Street Blues" from 1959 delight you. Dean Martins smooth vocal stylings will enthrall you as he performs the jazz standard "Wrap Your Troubles In Dreams". Witness the electrifying energy of Sammy Davis Jr.s performance of "Too Close For Comfort". Join us for this unforgettable musical experience that youll surely cherish!

programme.title: STUFF. live at BIRD Rotterdam
programme.desc: Rotterdams BIRD is a club, cafe, and restaurant with a live music program thats deeply rooted in jazz, soul, funk, hip-hop, and electronic. Its name BIRD refers to the nickname of legendary New York jazz saxophonist, bebop co-founder Charlie Parker. BIRD serves Neapolitan pizzas, fine wines, no-nonsense beers, and an all-round metropolitan rawness. Since 2014, this urban jazz club and DJAZZ.tv have been collaborating for a series of music programs: BIRD.tv, allowing you to experience the best BIRD concerts and interviews as from a first-row seat! Discover an irresistible live act; STUFF is full of unflagging energy. The Belgian band was founded in 2012 when drummer Lander Gyselinck was asked to play live music between DJ sets at a local bar. He gathered a bunch of friends, who also were musicians. The band could be considered an avant-garde jazz band who play a mix of funk, hip-hop, and electro. Andrew Claes (saxophone), Dries Laheye (bass guitar), Lander Gyselinck (drums), Mixmonster Menno (samples), and Joris Caluwaerts (keyboards) share an exceptional connection in music. They take over every stage and melt the hearts of music lovers.

programme.title: Portrait of Roy Ayers
programme.desc: "The legend of the groove" is a series of documentaries devoted to the musicians who were most influential on contemporary hip hop, soul, rhythm n blues, and on the course of history. Between the late 1950s and now, these musicians radically changed music. Although sometimes hardly in the public eye, they have all been major sources of inspiration for todays major artists: Prince, Erykah Badu, Janis Joplin and Jimi Hendrix.

programme.title: Tribute to Django Reinhardt
programme.sub-title: Tribute to Django Reinhardt: Rosenberg meets Beets
programme.desc: Bireli Lagrène is a French jazz guitarist born on September 4, 1966 in a family of gypsy tradition. His brother and his father introduced him from an early age to the repertoire of Django Reinhardt, whose influence is still felt in the style of Lagrène. In this performance, Lagrène pays homage to Django Reinhardt with his son, Babik Reinhardt.

programme.title: The MotorMusic Jazz Sessions
programme.desc: In this unique series,The MotorMusic Studios in Mechelen, Belgium, exert a magnetic attraction on countless first class jazz musicians. Where many of them visit international jazz musicians who share their views of their music with us.

programme.title: North Sea Jazz Classics
programme.desc: Registration of the performance of the Ahmad Jamal Trio at North Sea Jazz on July 16.

programme.title: Da Pá Virada Sessions
programme.desc: The series Da Pá Virada sessions presents the best musicians of contemporary Brazilian jazz, and beyond. Filmed in Sao Paulo, each session offers a unique experience by giving a fresh look into Brazils music scene. The artists for each session are selected in consultation with Stingray DJAZZs music editor.

programme.title: DJAZZ Clips
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Thomas Carbou
programme.desc: Thomas Carbou and Patrick Graham share an almost telepathic rapport, blending spontaneous improvisation, electronic looping, and Brazilian and Indian musical influences to create ecstatic groove pieces and dream-like soundscapes. They use a wide array of instruments, including a custom-built 8-string guitar, cuatro, bouzouki, cajon, frame drums, berimbau, udu, and metal percussion instruments, as well as samplers and laptops, adding their own hypnotic vocals to the mix. This concert was recorded at Montreals Le Bleury Vinyl Bar, near the Place des Festivals, known worldwide as the venue for the Montreal International Jazz Festival.

programme.title: Chamber Music
programme.desc: Hailing from a long tradition of Malian kora players, Ballake Sissoko has worked with renowned musicians such as Toumani Diabate and Taj Mahal. He met the French born Vincent Segal by chance, and the two began jamming together, uncertain of what kind of music might result. As a former member of the French National Orchestra, Segals Western classical training does not prevent him from exploring a wide variety of extended techniques, rendering his cello a flexible partner to Sissokos kora. A childhood spent in the Pigalle district of Paris surrounded by immigrant communities exposed Segal to African music from an early age. As such, he possesses a natural sensitivity to Sissokos West-African style. The concert shows a brilliant interplay between the two musicians and combines the several worlds of jazz, Malian and classical music.

programme.title: Paradox Live
programme.sub-title: Paradox Live: Jeroen van Vliet Moon Trio
programme.desc: Innovative contemporary jazz and improvised music, the search for modernity, mind blowing sounds, rock and pop… Indeed PARADOX Tilburg goes beyond jazz, crossing musical boundaries into the unknown soundscapes of electronic music. Indie artists, blues veterans and jazz superstars all pour their hearts and souls at the Paradox. From young, local talents to top national and international artists, PARADOX Tilburg is the most intimate jazz club in the Netherlands, with a devoted audience from all across Europe. In the TV show PARADOX LIVE you get a taste of the greatest concerts and interviews with artists from all around the world. This episode of PARADOX LIVE presents the amazing Dutch pianist Jeroen van Vliet.

programme.title: Bayerischer Hof Night Club
programme.sub-title: Bayerischer Hof Night Club: Maria Joao Quartet
programme.desc: In this recording, the Portuguese singer Maria Joao makes her appearance at the Bayerischer Hof Night Club during the 1999 Munchner Klaviersommer. She is accompanied by Marcio Doctor (percussion), Miroslav Tadic (guitar), and her long-standing partner, the brilliant pianist Mário Laginha. Maria is known for her vocal flexibility and improvisational skills. While normally considered a jazz artist, her music incorporates a mix of folk, ethnic music, modern jazz, avant-garde, electronica, symphonic and other genres. In this intimate venue, Joaos vocally and physically dynamic performance creates an electrifying atmosphere.

programme.title: Belgium Sessions
programme.desc: In this DJAZZ Belgium Sessions performance, which was recorded at AED Studios in Lint, Belgium, we witness Europes finest jazz musicians at work. A wide variety of international jazz musicians give a creative, up-close and inside insight into their art of playing jazz music. Young talent and established jazz musicians play to their hearts content: take for instance this unusual performance by the multi-ethnic ensemble Hijaz. This band explores the dialogue between piano and the oud, a pear-shaped stringed instrument from the East. Hijaz is a close-knit quartet that explores the differences and similarities between Mediterranean cultures in order to create moments of harmony, warmth, and great musical beauty.

programme.title: DJAZZ Clips
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Bill Evans - Maison de la Radio
programme.desc: Bill Evans is considered one of the greatest jazz pianists all time and is known for interpreting the jazz repertoire using impressionistic harmonies. In 1958, Evans first played in Miles Daviss sextet recording the modal jazz album "Kind of Blue", which is now considered one of the best jazz albums of all time. After leaving the ensemble, Evans formed several trios. In this concert, recorded at Maison de la Radio in Paris in 1972, Evans performs with his longest standing trio, featuring Eddie Gomez on double bass and Marty Morell on drums. The program features some of Evanss own compositions, including the jazz waltz "Very Early" and the modal jazz piece "Time Remembered", as well as jazz standard "Autumn Leaves".

programme.title: North Sea Jazz Classics
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, internationally known as a festival where the past, present and future of jazz are discussed in three days. Besides a good dose of jazz, other genres are also programmed, including blues, soul, funk, and hip-hop. In 1981 the American singer and Grammy Award winner Al Jarreau gave an unforgettable performance for the enthusiastic audience of the North Sea Jazz Festival in The Hague.

programme.title: WOMEX 2018
programme.desc: Since 1994, World Music Expo (WOMEX) has been attracting musicians, agents, a great number of press agencies, as well as media companies from all over the world. Its main exposition event has been held in various locations throughout Europe, including Berlin, Brussels, Marseille, Stockholm, Seville, Cardiff, and Budapest. In 2018, WOMEX was held in Las Palmas, Gran Canaria.

programme.title: PC Qwintett
programme.desc: Pierre Courbois has been one of Europes leading jazz musicians since the mid-sixties. This concert, recorded at the renowned Amsterdam jazz club Bimhuis, sees the drummer playing with his QWINTETT. On the occasion of his 75th birthday in 2015, Courbois hit the road for the Pierre Courbois 75 Years Anniversary Tour. The PC QWINTETT consists of several highly acclaimed Dutch jazz musicians with whom Courbois has worked before in his long and versatile career. Among them are pianist Nike Langenhuijsen, double bassist Egon Kracht, trumpeter Toon de Gouw, and trombonist Ilja Reijngoud. QWINTETT honours the Charles Mingus tradition of thematic and melodic ensemble jazz - but also with an unmistakable Courbois groove! Courbois, known for his own way of combining compositions with improvisations, melodically melts constructions with uneven breaks.

programme.title: Rita Reys and The Pim Jacobs Trio at North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is well known for its worldwide broad programming from traditional New Orleans Jazz, swing, bop ,free jazz, fusion, avant-garde and electronic jazz to blues, gospel, funk, soul, RandB, hip-hop, world beat and latin. The three day festival was organised by Paul Acket whom gained his fortune as a publisher of pop music magazines in the 1960s.

programme.title: Estival Jazz Lugano
programme.desc: Since 1977, Estival is a summer jazz festival in Switzerland, Lugano. Estival offers a thrilling and particularly surprising line-up that explores the rich world of contemporary music whilst promoting the understanding of different cultures, tolerance, and co-existence. The composer, trumpeter and bugle player Franco Ambrosetti performs with his quintet in his native Lugano as part of the Estival.

programme.title: TorTube
programme.sub-title: TorTube: Dual City Concert Band ft. Hermine Deurlo
programme.desc: Jazz fans in television land have come to the right place for their dose of first-rate world jazz: TorTube! Jazz club De Tor in Enschede is one of Europes most authentic jazz venues, with an absolutely unique ambiance. Some of the best musicians from Holland and the rest of the world find their way to De Tor to perform for an appreciative audience of jazz fans. Foot Together is a TorTube episode featuring Dutch jazz icon Hermine Deurloo on the chromatic harmonica, in collaboration with the Dual City Concert Band led by Rini Swinkels. The spirited big band plays swinging and powerful jazz, with the incredible Hermine Deurloo adding a touch of Toots Thielemans as she plays her Hohner Toots Mellow Tone mouth organ.

programme.title: McCoy Tyner Trio live at Estival Lugano
programme.desc: Since 1977, Estival is a summer jazz festival in Switzerland, Lugano. Estival offers a thrilling and particularly surprising line-up that explores the rich world of contemporary music whilst promoting the understanding of different cultures, tolerance, and co-existence. McCoy Tyners first main exposure came with Benny Golson, being the first pianist in Golsons and Art Farmers Jazztet. Hes also known for his work with the John Coltrane Quartet. Tyners style is easily comparable to Coltranes maximalist style of saxophone. Though a member of Coltranes group, he was never overshadowed by the saxophonist, but complemented and even inspired Coltranes open-minded approach. McCoy Tyner is considered one of the most influential jazz pianists of the 20th century, an honour he earned both with Coltrane and in his years of performing following Coltranes death.

programme.title: Live at A to JazZ Festival
programme.sub-title: Live at A to JazZ Festival: Sofia
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic "stretch music"; an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuahs quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: The Morgenland Festival
programme.sub-title: The Morgenland Festival: The Art of Duo
programme.desc: Since 2005, the Morgenland Festival of Osnabrueck has dedicated itself to the fascinating music culture of the Near and Middle East. From traditional and classical music to avant-garde, jazz, and rock, the festival program also features art, such as visual arts, dance, and theatre of interdisciplinary projects. "The Art of Duo" presents an unprecedented duo featuring pianist Salman Gambarov and sheng player, a Chinese mouth-organ, Wu Wei.

programme.title: Aki Rissanen Trio at Jazzclub Unterfahrt, Munich
programme.desc: Aki Rissanens interest in jazz came after he started taking classical piano lessons. His deep interest in improvised music placed him among top jazz pianist in his home country - Finland. While composing and performing his own music, Rissanen has also collaborated with Verneri Pohjola and Dave Liebman, and today his name appears among the top European jazz musicians. Live from "Jazzclub Unterfahrt" in Munich, Germany, together with Antti Lotjonen on bass and Teppo Makynen on drums, Rissanen showcases the best of Scandinavian jazz and its DNA - the Nordic Tone.

programme.title: Ella Fitzgerald in Brussels
programme.sub-title: Ella Fitzgerald in Brussels: The American Songbook
programme.desc: Ella Fitzgerald: Live in "57" features "The First Lady Of Song" in a distinct performance. Its the earliest known complete concert of Ella to be captured on film. Shot in Belgium, this 1957 concert sees her performing with jazz greats Ray Brown, Herb Ellis, Jo Jones and the legendary Oscar Peterson on classics such as "Lullaby Of Birdland" and It Dont Mean A Thing (If It Aint Got That Swing). Although she wanted to be a dancer at first, Ella Fitzgerald already listened to recordings of Louis Armstrong, Bing Crosby and The Boswell Sisters at an early age. After her debut at an amateur talent show in 1934, Ella joined Chick Webbs Orchestra with which she recorded several hits; after Webb died, she became the leader of the orchestra. In the late 1940s, Ella Fitzgerald became known as the First Lady of Song, with her wide vocal range of three octaves. The American jazz singer was particularly appreciated for her pure tone, intonation and phrasing, and unparalleled improvisational abilities. In a career that spanned close to 60 years, Fitzgerald sold 40 million albums and won 13 Grammy Awards, mainly for her definitive interpretations of the Great American Songbook.

programme.title: Live at the Metro Theatre
programme.desc: Angus and Julia Stone are an Australian brother-sister folk-blues group which formed in 2006. Their parents played as a folk duo before Julia and Angus were born. Angus and Julia Stone have released two studio albums, A Book Like This (8 September 2007), which peaked at No. 6 on the ARIA Albums Chart; and Down. Here they perform at The Metro Theatre, in Sydney, Australia, on October 10, 2007.

programme.title: DJAZZ Portrait
programme.desc: These portraits of artists, concerts and festivals give a good impression of the jazz world. Both famous and less famous jazz artists will give a new insight in their life. DJAZZ asked them why they wrote that special song, what was the first record they bought and what is his or her most precious musical memory. The festival portraits are beautiful reports filmed at the most special jazz festivals and concerts. They revive the memory of the festival, the music and the experience.

programme.title: Dionne Warwick live at the 27 Club
programme.desc: Dionne Warwicks vocal artistry ranges from voluminous deep register to soft, fragile high notes. She masters the entire range with almost unnerving ease. But more than her strong, warm voice, Dionnes magic is in the silky elegance and the secure delivery with which she tells a story. Thats how her, along with composer Burt Bacharach and lyricist Hal David become pioneers of the brand of pop music called "Middle of the Road", meaning pop that is grippingly simple, but never trite. Sixty of her hits made it into the American charts and sold over 100 million albums worldwide. This amazing 1964 recording from the 27 Club in Knokke, Belgium showcases the 23-year-old star vocalist at the start of her career.

programme.title: Terrasson and Belmondo
programme.sub-title: Terrasson and Belmondo: À Nous Garo
programme.desc: Every year, the Jazz en Baie festival takes place in the beautiful bay of Mont Saint-Michel Todays broadcast shows a special gathering between two grandmasters of French jazz: pianist Jacky Terrasson and trumpeter Stephane Belmondo. The two team up for an amazing concert in which jazz is combined with soul and a touch of chanson française. The Franco-American pianist Terrasson delights in travelling the world, collaboration with others and leading his own trio, quartet, or quintet. With his long-time friend, Stephane Belmondo, Terrasson has produced wonderful CDs and beautiful concerts. One then finds the trumpeter on the pianists album Gouache; on another, the pianist guests on Belmondos Ever After. At the Jazz en Baie festival, the duo plays its amazing piano and trumpet music. Highly recommended!

programme.title: BIRD - The Nest
programme.desc: Five promising musicians get together in Rotterdam jazz club BIRDs artists-in-residence project "The Nest". Over the course of seven sessions, these talents exchange ideas, work on their projects, and play music together. Following this period, during which record producer Jameszoo and music manager Jochem Tromp offer their coaching experience, BIRD and North Sea Jazz Festivals fringe festival DownTown organize a tryout performance. In this short documentary, the artists share their impressions from the project. They introduce themselves, reveal why they joined The Nest and formulate what they hope to learn from the experience. Naturally, we get a glimpse of the songs they wrote during the sessions, as performed during the tryout show. Featuring Lisette Ma Neza (slam poet), Peter Somuah (trumpet), Michelle Samba (drums), Huy Le (bass), and Brenn Luiten (piano).

programme.title: Jazzwoche Burghausen
programme.desc: Every year since 1970, the German city of Burghausen has been hosting one of the largest jazz festivals in the world. During Burghausen International Jazz Week, Burghausen becomes a Bavarian jazz mecca: guests from all over the world join the Burghausers to enjoy the most wonderful jazz performances as the colorful hustle and bustle of spectators and musicians shake up the city. One of the bands performing here in 2019 is the Walter Trout Band. Trout, who was born in New Jersey and is based in Los Angeles, is a world-famous contemporary blues rock guitarist and vocalist.

programme.title: Jungle By Night - Jazz in Duketown
programme.desc: Jazz in Duketown is the largest free outdoor jazz festival in the Netherlands. Its a real gathering for jazz addicts, inviting internationally renowned bands. In 2019, one of them is the Amsterdam-based Dutch instrumental collective Jungle by Night. The band plays a mix of various styles, inspired by funk, jazz, dub, rock and others. The ensemble made its debut in 2010 and has played at numerous festivals. Their December 2010 performance with former backing musicians of Afrobeat founder Fela Kuti in Paris saw them hailed as "the future of Afrobeat".

programme.title: Arsenik - Olympia, Paris
programme.desc: The mythical duo Arsenik is a rap group from France, made up of two brothers, Lino and Calbo. The team performs at Olympia Paris to celebrate their 20 years since their first album, Quelques gouttes suffisent… Its a unique concert: Arsenik plays the entire album with numerous special guests for the first time. The album has sold over 300,000 copies in France. Today its being considered a classic, and it continues to be cited in the top five of the best French rap albums of all generations. Enjoy Arseniks live show in Olympia Paris!

programme.title: Woody Hermans Swinging Herd live in England 1964
programme.desc: Woody Herman: Live in 64 features a blistering one-hour concert from 1964 showcasing one of the very hottest line-ups of the "Swinging Herd," including trumpeter Bill Chase, trombonist Phil Wilson, and the amazing saxophonist Sal Nistico on the front line, as well as drummer Jake Hanna, bassist Chuck Andrus, and pianist-arranger Nat Pierce in the rhythm section. The band roars throughout the entire show which includes standards such as "Lonesome Old Town", "After Youve Gone", and new originals including Charles Minguss "Better Git It In Your Soul."

programme.desc: The world-renowned North Sea Jazz Festival features a wide variety of genres, including traditional New Orleans jazz, swing, bop, free jazz, fusion, avant-garde and electronic jazz, blues, gospel, funk, soul, RandB, hip hop, world beat and Latin. The festival was founded by entrepreneur and jazz fan Paul Acket, who sold his highly successful pop magazine publishing house to organize and fund the first edition of the festival in 1976. This broadcast from the North Sea Jazz Archives presents the amazing Dizzy Gillespie, accompanied by The Skymasters.

programme.title: Tribute to Django Reinhardt
programme.sub-title: Tribute to Django Reinhardt: Bireli Lagrene
programme.desc: Bireli Lagrène is a French jazz guitarist born on September 4, 1966 in a family of gypsy tradition. His brother and his father introduced him from an early age to the repertoire of Django Reinhardt, whose influence is still felt in the style of Lagrène. In this performance, Lagrène pays homage to Django Reinhardt with his son, Babik Reinhardt.

programme.title: Dave Brubeck and Paul Desmond live in Belgium
programme.desc: Dave Brubeck: Live in 64 boasts a beautifully filmed concert from one of the most beloved quartets in jazz history. Captured at the pinnacle of their power and popularity, Paul Desmond (alto sax), Joe Morello (drums), Eugene Wright (bass) and Dave Brubeck (piano) explore the trails they blazed into the realm of odd time signatures with "Forty Days" and two versions of their groundbreaking hit Take Five, as well as forays into world music with a unique interpretation of Koto Song. Their intimate onstage chemistry and impeccable musicianship made the DBQ an award-winning jazz supergroup.

programme.title: La nuit des gitans
programme.desc: The Royal Conservatoire of Liège hosted a "Night of the Gypsies" at the International Guitar Festival of Liège in 1995. At this occasion, the Raphaël Faÿs Trio and Quintet paid tribute to Romani-Belgian jazz guitarist Django Reinhardt. Raphaël Faÿs (solo guitar), Pierre Blanchard (violin), Daniel Manzanas (guitar), Pablo Gilabert (bass) and Miguel Sanchez (percussion) play Reinhardts greatest gypsy jazz hits, including It Had To Be You, How High The Moon, Sweet Georgia Brown, and Minor Swing. Enjoy Raphaël Faÿss fresh take on the light-fingered string sound and swinging rhythms of Django Reinhardts gypsy jazz!

programme.title: Louis "Satchmo" Armstrong and His All Stars
programme.desc: Louis Armstrong: Live in 59 is one of the only known complete Armstrong concerts from the 1950s to be captured on film. This 55-minute set, filmed in Belgium in 1959, features many of Satchmos greatest songs including Mack The Knife, When Its Sleepy Time Down South and "Stompin" At The Savoy, backed by his stellar band the All-Stars, featuring Trummy Young, Peanuts Hucko, Billy Kyle, Danny Barcelona and Mort Herbert.

programme.desc: Piano and saxophone - this is an individualistic jazz duo combination. But the melodiousness and maturity of Charlie Marianos saxophone and the freshness and feistiness of Wolfgang Dauners piano turn the meeting of these two jazz greats into a thrilling interplay.

programme.title: The Morgenland Festival
programme.desc: Since 2005, the Morgenland Festival of Osnabrueck has dedicated itself to the fascinating music culture of the Near and Middle East. From traditional and classical music to avant-garde, jazz, and rock, the festival program also features art, such as visual arts, dance, and theatre of interdisciplinary projects. "Viva" is a perfect mixture of various instruments and musicians from all over the world. Vocalists Aynur and Dima Oshno perform with the All Star Band. Aynur sings about the life and sufferings of Kurdish people, in particular Kurdish women. Musically, she tries to blend Kurdish and Western music, creating her own style and interpreting the traditional repertoire in a modern and fresh way.

programme.title: Sarah Vaughan Live in 58 and 64
programme.sub-title: Sarah Vaughan Live in 58 and 64: The Divine One
programme.desc: Sarah Vaughan: Live in 58 and 64 features the "Divine One" in her prime, wrapping her sultry voice around jazz standards such as Lover Man, "Misty" and "I Got Rhythm" and soaring on popular showtunes such as "Over The Rainbow" and Maria. One of the greatest voices of the 20th Century, her renditions of songs by Harold Arlen, Leonard Bernstein, Johnny Burke, the Gershwins and Stephen Sondheim are pure diva magic. These three performances demonstrate why Sarah Vaughan is invariably mentioned in the same breath as Ella Fitzgerald and Billie Holiday.

programme.title: Georgie Fame and the Blue Flames
Milt Jacksons Modern Jazz Quartet at the Bozar
programme.desc: The Modern Jazz Quartet (MJQ) was composed of Milt "Bags" Jackson on vibraphone, John Lewis on piano, Percy Heath on bass, and Connie Kay on drums. Milt Jackson and John Lewis were pioneer bebop musicians who had played together in Dizzy Gillespies 1948 big band. They pursued separate careers before adding Heath and Lewis to form the Modern Jazz Quartet in the 1950s. Noted for its delicate percussion sonorities, innovative jazz forms, and high performance standards, the MJQ was an immensely popular jazz and "third stream" ensemble until its final concerts in the early 1990s.

programme.title: La Mambanegra - Music Meeting Festival 2018
programme.desc: The latin music orchestra, La Mambanegra, combines many musical elements, such as Jamaican or Colombian music, as well as Funk and Hip Hop. Yet, their main musical influence comes from 1970s New York, where during the time Salsa was born. The magic of the genre, however, is given new colours by La Mambanegra: with a series of fantastic adventures in Cali, La Habana and New York, the bands music is inspired by an anonymous and even mythical hero of the Calis popular neighborhood Barrio Obrero. Consisting of 8 talented musicians, La Mambanegra presents their charming showcase at the Music Meeting Festival in Nijmegen, The Netherlands.

programme.title: Michelle David - Jazz in Duketown
programme.desc: Jazz in Duketown is the largest free outdoor jazz festival in the Netherlands. Its a real gathering for jazz addicts, inviting internationall renowned artists. The talented American singer Michelle David performs pop and gospel music that feeds the heart and soothes the soul. Having grown up with the church, she started singing at the age of four. A year later she joined her first band, The Mission of Love. In 1980 she enrolled at Fiorello H. LaGuardia High School of Music and Art and Performing Arts in New York City, known from the film Fame. During this time, she appeared as an extra in the legendary comedy film Ghostbusters. Musicals and tours with the bands of Diana Ross and Michael Bolton followed.

Villas ellujaamiseks peavad saarlased olema paaris mõne teise saarlasega ning sooritama erinevaid valjakutseid. Võitnud paar saab endale 56 000 eurot.

programme.title: Poissmees paradiisis
programme.desc: Mõned sidemed tugevnevad, mõned leegid kustuvad. Üks poissmees kasutab viimast võimalust, et tagada endale kohta saarel.

programme.title: Lotovõitja unistuste kodu
programme.desc: Kahemiljoniline lotovõit võimaldab paaril oma lemmiksuvituskohast teha oma alalise teise kodu. David Bromstad tõttab neile appi, et leida see tapselt õige maja jarve aares.

programme.title: Pilvede all
programme.desc: Indrek ei mõista Mari otsust Romani suhtes, kuid õigustab ennast Riina osas. Valter paneb Kertu keerulisse olukorda. Albert on Pireti kaitumisest nordinud. Urmas saab aru, et Gunnar plaanib midagi. Andres toob lapsed koju, kuid Kertuga kohtumine võtab oodatust hoopis erineva poorde.

programme.title: Vana silla saladus
programme.desc: Don Ignacio rundab Consuelot. Fe loeb Mauricio kirju. Doloresel on Tiburciole ettepanek.

programme.title: Esmakohtingud teismelistele
programme.desc: Sõjavaekadett Eve tahab poissi, kes armastab muusikat. Caelum on oma esimesel kohtingul transmehena.

programme.title: Kodus ja võõrsil
programme.desc: Bronte skeemitamine tasub end ara. Kas Mackenzie õpib Levit usaldama? Edeni viha ei lahtu.

programme.title: Igavene armastus
programme.desc: Tarik parib Nihanilt oma õe tulistamise kohta. Zeynepi tulistaja ule mõistetakse kohut. Emir kuuleb Nihani autoõnnetuse kohta uudiseid.

programme.title: Toidu ABC
programme.sub-title: Parim 1: datlid, mandlid, või ja haggis
programme.desc: Purustame toiduainete kohta keerlevaid muute ja laseme teaduslikel argumentidel kõnelda.

programme.title: Toidu ABC
programme.sub-title: Parim 2: kuivatatud ploomid, must pipar ja Šveitsi juust
programme.desc: Purustame toiduainete kohta keerlevaid muute ja laseme teaduslikel argumentidel kõnelda.

programme.title: Inga Lindstrom
programme.desc: Luisa mees Stefan suundub valisreisile ega poordu enam koju tagasi. Korraga leiab Luisa end uksikema rollist, kuid lapsehoidjat pole kerge leida. Kui tema ukse taga seisab mees nimega Ben, peab naine teda lapsehoidja kandidaadiks. Tegelikkuses end agendi eest peitev kirjanik kasutab võimaluse ara. Sellega pole kaos veel lõppenud, sest ootamatusi ja mehi jagub Luisa ellu veel.

programme.title: Kood 7500
programme.desc: Kui terroristid uritavad Berliini-Pariisi lennu ule kontrolli haarata, puuab leebe ameeriklasest kaaspiloot paasta reisijate ja meeskonna elusid, luues samal ajal ullatava sideme uhe kaaperdajaga.

programme.title: Kaks kanget Lõuna-Ameerikas
programme.desc: Humoorika seiklus-saate teises osas jõuab seljakotirandur Teet loodussõprade unistustemaale - samal ajal kohtub hotelliturist Kristjan Equadori presidendiga ja kulastab kohalikku relvapoodi, naeme kuidas pidutsevad kohalikud ja kuidas ausad Eesti mehed.

programme.title: Isamees
programme.desc: Marulipõnevik! Keset pulmi rundavad palgasõdurid kuurorthotelli ning peigmees, isamees ja nende purjus parim sõber peavad asuma paeva paastma.

programme.title: Silmapete
programme.desc: Wahrend eines Boxkampfes ist Detective Rick Santoro fur die Sicherheit des US-Verteidigungsministers verantwortlich. Da fallt der Politiker einem Heckenschutzen zum Opfer. Es gelingt zwar, den Morder zu toten, doch nach einigen vorerst unerklarlichen Zwischenfallen beginnt Santoro an der Einzeltater-Theorie zu zweifeln. Umgehend lasst er die Arena sperren – 14.000 Menschen werden zu Verdachtigen.

programme.title: Unustamatu 2024
programme.desc: Aasta hakkab lõppema ning on aeg heita pilk tahavaatepeeglisse. 30. detsembril jõuab Kanal 2 ekraanile vaatajate seas vaga populaarne erisaade, mis võtab kokku aasta kõige põrutavad sundmused, mis niipea ei unune. Aastal 2024 sai Eesti rahvas nautida Tartus Euroopa Kulutuuripealinna tiitliga kaasnevat melu, kiita või kiruda uusi makse, elada olumpiamangudel kaasa meie sportlastele ming jalgida poliitmelu nii kodumaal kui ka USA-s. Aastat võtavad kokku Anu Saagim, Erik Moora, Elo Mõttus-Leppik, Neeme Raud, Maria Rannavali, Kristjan Gold, Juku Kalle-Raid ja Ott Jarvela.

programme.title: Meie inimesed
programme.desc: Kuni 35. eluaastani oli Tallinnas elav venelanna Ella taiskohaga koduperenaine. Siis aga võttis ta katte ja asus õppima ettevõtlusega seonduvat. Tana, kaks aastat hiljem, on naise eesmargiks luua pealinna peamiselt venekeelsele elanikkonnale mõeldud koolituskeskus. Režissoor Marten Vaher, autor-toimetaja Mirjam Matiisen, produtsent Hannela Lippus.

programme.title: Tana õhtul...
programme.desc: Inimesena suur, soe ja sõbralik. Lauljana sugav, siiras ja võrratu. Uno Loobi kõrval oli Vello Orumets meie teine urghiiglane, keda estraadi marutuuled ei suutnud 50 aastaga maha murda. Saatejuht Vahur Kersna, režissoor Tarvo Molder. Tana on Vello Orumetsa 80. sunniaastapaev.

programme.title: Elmar TV
programme.desc: Raadiost Elmar tuttav Eesti muusika kullafond ja ka varsked kodumaised hitid hoiavad Eesti Kanalis oositi tuju uleval. Nostalgitse või laula kaasa, kodumaiste muusikavideote paremik on eetris!

programme.title: Murdochi musteeriumid

programme.title: Murdochi musteeriumid
programme.desc: Jargmisel hommikul parast seda, kui Ogden osaleb kergejõustikuuritusel, kus teatati plaanist viia naiskond 1912. aasta Stockholmi olumpiamangudele, leiab treener valjakult surnuna uhe meessportlase.

programme.title: Noor inspektor Morse

programme.title: Miss Marple
programme.desc: Jacko Argyle suri vanglas parast seda, kui ta mõisteti suudi oma kasuema mõrvamises. Dr Arthur Carlgary suudab aga tõestada, et Jacko oli mõrvamise hetkel tema juures, mis tahendab, et ta oli suutu mees.

programme.title: Miss Marple
programme.desc: Miss Marple kulastab oma kooliaegset sõbrannat ja satub kahtlaste surmajuhtumite keerisesse. Kulaliste seas on ka tennisetaht oma endise ja praeguse naisega ning keegi ei saa hasti aru, kellega ta sisuliselt koos elab.

programme.title: Preili Scarlet ja Hertsog
programme.desc: Lugu sellest, kuidas kõik alguse sai, algab 12 aastat varem, kui Hertsog ja Eliza esimest korda kohtusid.

programme.title: Grantchester
programme.desc: Vikaar Sidney Chambers ja kohalik inspektor Geordie Keating lahendavad 1950ndate aastate Grantchesteri kulas kuritegusid. programme.title: Miss Marple
programme.desc: Miss Marple satub oma suurima valjakutse otsa, kui ta saab oma surnud sõbralt Rafielilt juhtnoorid uurida võimalikku kuritegu. Ometi ei sisalda see vihje mingit infot, millise kuritooga võib tegemist olla.

programme.title: Suured loomad, vaiksed loomad
programme.desc: James Herriot otsustab viia ellu oma unistuse saada loomaarstiks: ta sõidab Darrowbysse, teadmata tapselt, kus see koht asub ja millega tegu. programme.title: Madal haud
programme.desc: R: Danny Boyle. O: Ewan McGregor, Christopher Eccleston. Kolm sõpra avastavad, et nende uus korterikaaslane on mustilisel kombel surnud ja maha jatnud kohvritaie raha. Meeleheitlikult laibale sobivat asukohta otsides hakkavad sõprade vahele tekkima esimesed hõõrdumised, mis viivad ootamatute tagajargedeni. Hinnatud lavastaja Danny Boylei ("Rentslimiljonar", "127 tundi") debuutmangufilm andis uue hingamise moodunud sajandi lõpuaastate inglise krimikomoodia žanrile, mida iseloomustas cooli valjapeetusega ehtbritilik musta huumoriga vurtsitatud stiil. Filmi edust said karjaaris tuule tiibadesse nii lavastaja Boyle, stsenaariumi autor John Hodges kui ka noor naitleja Ewan McGregor, kes kõik koos seisid ka 1996. aastal kinosid tormtulena vallutanud filmi "Trainspotting" tegemise taga.

programme.title: Queen Budapestis. Hungarian Rhapsody
programme.desc: 27. juulil 1986. aastal andis Queen Budapesti Nepstadiumil kõigi aegade suurima staadionikontserdi. Sundmus oli sedavõrd oluline, et selle jaadvustasid Ungari tippoperaatorid ja tehnikud. Filmile salvestatud kontserti on nuud võimalik vaadata HD-kvaliteedis.

programme.title: Karu Karla
programme.desc: Vahva sari kolmeaastastest lastest ja nende parimast sõbrast Karu-Karlast. Karla on laste lemmikkaisukaru, kes arkab ellu ainult siis, kui kedagi teist lahedal pole. Karla aitab vaikestel põnnidel ule saada igasugustest hirmudest ja muredest, ning teeb seda parimal võimalikul viisil - killukese maagia ja kujutlusvõimega.

programme.title: Aasta tipphetked 2024
programme.desc: Millisena jaab meelde 2024. aasta kultuuri- ja meelelahutuse vallas? Kindlasti on see olnud Tartu kui Euroopa kultuuripealinna aasta. Aga see on olnud ka juubelite aasta, sest naiteks Tartu suusamaraton tahistas 50. ja ansambel Jam 30. sunnipaeva. See oli ka hea filmiaasta, mistõttu režissoor Jaak Kilmi raagib, kui palju ja millist vastukaja sai "Vari" ning Mart Sander meenutab, kuidas tema oma filmiga Guinnessi rekordite raamatusse paases. Aga mismoodi Banksy uhke naitus Tallinna toodi, miks 2024. aasta oli ka kosmiliselt põnev ja palju muudki mahub aasta elamusi kokkuvõtvasse saatesse. Toimetajad Priit Rajalo ja Teet Teder, režissoor Rahel Selge, produtsent Heiki Sepp.

programme.title: Noor meister

Saatejuht Piret Krumm, režissoor Kristo Veinberg, toimetaja Sigrid Salutee, tootja ULM OÜ.

Tom seisab selles karmis valjakutses silmitsi ka iseendaga.

Seda teab ka Bettina Dewald ehk Betty, kompetentne ja resoluutne õde, kes ei tunne aukartust kellegi ees. Ta utleb, mida arvab, ja teeb, mida utleb.

Saatejuht Meelis Oidsalu vaatab koos naitleja Indrek Ojari, psuhholoog Mati Heidmetsa ja kultuuriloolase Marju Kõivupuuga filmis ohtralt kasutatud vagisõnade taha: mis neid ropendada ja kakelda armastavaid tuupe kaivitab ning mida on sel tanastegi teismeliste lemmikuks olevas filmis uldse kultuurset?

programme.title: Lainud on jaanud
programme.desc: New Delhis sundinud režissoor Varun Trikha randas aastaid kaameraga Setomaal, et jaadvustada sealsete inimeste lugusid ning nende suhestumist mineviku ja olevikuga. Riigipiiride tõttu lõhkikistud ajalooline Petserimaa on paik, mis paneb mõtisklema kaotusest, eraldusest, lahkumissunnist ning soovist oma kultuuriga taas uhendust leida. Kuue aasta valtel tõmbab Varun Trikhat ikka ja jalle tagasi kolme kohaliku asuka juurde, kes on otsustanud jaada sellele eikellegimaale. Nad ullatavad teda lugudega oma unenagudest, mis moodunut ja poordumatult kaotatut leevendavad. Omaparasel moel aratavad need lood ules ka režissoori enda malestused ja otsingud. Ühel ool, huljatud majas peavarju leidnuna, naeb ta salaparast und oma ammulahkunud vanaisast, keda ta pole kunagi kohanud, ning ta otsustab valja selgitada, kes tema vanaisa tegelikult oli. Oma poeetilises, visuaalselt ja tahenduskihtidelt rikkas filmis paotab Varun Trikha unenaolise ukse korraga nii Eesti kui ka India uhiskonna haavadesse ning oma isiklikku perekonnalukku.

programme.desc: R: Danny Boyle. O: Ewan McGregor, Christopher Eccleston. Kolm sõpra avastavad, et nende uus korterikaaslane on mustilisel kombel surnud ja maha jatnud kohvritaie raha. Meeleheitlikult laibale sobivat asukohta otsides hakkavad sõprade vahele tekkima esimesed hõõrdumised, mis viivad ootamatute tagajargedeni. Hinnatud lavastaja Danny Boylei ("Rentslimiljonar", "127 tundi") debuutmangufilm andis uue hingamise moodunud sajandi lõpuaastate inglise krimikomoodia žanrile, mida iseloomustas cooli valjapeetusega ehtbritilik musta huumoriga vurtsitatud stiil. Filmi edust said karjaaris tuule tiibadesse nii lavastaja Boyle, stsenaariumi autor John Hodges kui ka noor naitleja Ewan McGregor, kes kõik koos seisid ka 1996. aastal kinosid tormtulena vallutanud filmi "Trainspotting" tegemise taga.

programme.title: Osoon
programme.desc: 2006. aastal sai Eesti valusa õppetunni seni kõige ulatuslikumast naftareostusest, mis meie rannikule jõudis. Toona ei osatud maardunud linde kuidagi aidata. Teeme kaasa eluslooduse reostustõrje õppuse ja selgitame, kuidas on tanaseks paranenud Eesti valmisolek selliste olukordade lahendamiseks. Taani Laanemere-aarse ranniku kalapuuk on haabumas. Kohtume kohalike kaluritega, kes veel seni pole oma kutsest loobunud ja uurime, kas neid kimbutavad sarnased probleemid, mis meie kalureid. Kaido Haagen jutustab loo oisest Kuningakulast, kus pole kull inimasustust, aga metsarahval kaib vilgas elu. Saate autorid on Kristo Elias ja Sander Loite, toimetaja Marit Valk, režissoor Keiti Valiste, produtsent Heiki Sepp.

programme.desc: Leseks jaanud briti arimees, hr Blake, asub ulemteenrina toole Prantsusmaal asuvas mõisahoones. Ta valib sellise ameti seetõttu, et soovib hoida ja elustada malestusi oma kadunud prantslannast abikaasast. Mehe elu võtab aga uusi poordeid, kui ta saab tuttavamaks mõisaproua ja majapidamispersonaliga, kes kõik on veidi omamoodi... Filmi peaosas sarab vanameister John Malkovich.

programme.title: Arabella, mereroovli tutar
programme.desc: Vaikese Arabella kodu pole tudrukule kasvamiseks just parim paik. Piraadilaeva kapteni Taaniel Tina tutrena on tal mitmetes asjades sõnaõigust. Kui merest tõmmatakse valja randaja Aadu, nõuab tudruk saagi endale. Randaja arusaam maailma asjadest on aga hoopis teine kui mereroovlitel ja aegamisi hakkab ka Taaniel Tina mõistma, et tudruk peaks kasvama rahumeelsemas keskkonnas. Kui Arabella konkurentide poolt roovitakse, algab tõeliselt ohtlik seiklus. Peeter Simmi lavastatud lastefilm tugineb Aino Perviku raamatule ja kuulub kahtlemata parimate Eesti (laste)filmide hulka. Ühendades nii seiklused kui ka inimlikkuse teema, loob film ainulaadse ja haarava maailma. Osades Kai Puskar, Lembit Peterson, Urmas Kibuspuu jt.

programme.title: Magomajev
programme.desc: 1960ndate lõpp. Parast Muslim Magomajevi võitu Sopoti laulufestivalil teevad prantslased noormehele ettepaneku esineda Pariisis kuulsas Olympia kontserdisaalis. Kultuuriminister Furtseva lubab Muslimi Pariisi oma isiklikul vastutusel ja tingimusel, et noormees kaitub nõukogude lauljale kohaselt ning jargib ametlikult kinnitatud repertuaari. Muslimile naivad tingimused ulearu ranged ja ta on valmis sõidust loobuma, kuid juhus muudab kõike. Ta tutvub võluva ooperitahe Tamara Sinjavskajaga ja noorte vahel tekib esimesest pilgust peale sade.

programme.desc: Mihhail Ivanovitš on teenekas pensionar, kes elab uksinda oma maamajas. Lapsed kaivad tal harva kulas. Ootamatult tulevad pojad naistega tema 67. sunnipaevale. programme.desc: Lugu USA sõjavae seersandist John Kinleyst ja Afganistani tõlgist Ahmedist. Ahmed paastab parast ootamatut runnakut kangelaslikult Kinley elu. Kui aga Kinley saab hiljem teada, et Ahmedi ja ta perekonda ei aidatudki lubatult Ameerikasse, tasub ta võla, minnes neid enne Talibani katte langemist paastma.

programme.title: John Wick 4
programme.desc: "John Wicki" seeria neljandas osas võtab John Wick (Keanu Reeves) ette siiani kõige ohtlikuma seikluse. Wick, kelle pea eest pakutakse aina rohkem raha, laheb gildi vastu globaalsesse sõtta, otsides allilma võimsamaid New Yorgist ja Pariisist kuni Oslo ja Berliinini valja.

programme.title: Kapten Fantastiline
programme.desc: Puhendunud isa Ben, kes kasvatab ja õpetab kuut last valjaspool tsivilisatsiooni, sugaval metsas ellu jaama, on sunnitud lahkuma sellest oma katega loodud paradiisist. Kokkupuutes reaalse maailmaga asub see seltskond teekonnale, mis seab kahtluse alla nii Beni arusaama tõelisest vabadusest, kui ka selle, mida tahendab perekond.

programme.title: Dora ja kadunud kuldlinn
programme.desc: USA, Mexico, Australia 2019 seiklus Lavastaja:James Bobin Osades: Isabela Merced, Eugenio Derbez, Michael Pena Olles veetnud suurema osa oma elust koos vanematega džunglit uurides, ei suutnud miski Dorat ette valmistada tema kõige ohtlikumaks seikluseks. Maadeavastaja Dora leiab end kiiresti Bootsit juhtimas, et paasta oma vanemad ja lahendada kadunud inkade tsivilisatsiooni võimatut saladust.

programme.title: Imedepark
programme.desc: USA,Hispaania 2019 animakomoodia Lavastaja:David Feiss Osades (haaled):Kirke Selirand (June), Marko Matvere (Mõmmu), Janek Joost (Steve), Mart Avandi (Gus), Ott Sepp (Cooper), Raimo Pass (Pahkel), Marilyn Jurman (Greta). Kujutle ebatavalist lõbustusparki, kus gravitatsiooni trotsivad karussellid, ameerika raudteed ja vaaterattad vuhistavad kilkavaid kulastajaid tuhinal labi õhu, tanavad on tais varvikaid tegelasi ja imetabased atraktsioonid panevad lapsed vaimustusest õhku ahmima. Just sellise lõputut lusti ja ullatusi tais Imedepargi mõtles valja 8-aastane matemaatika- ja inseriteaduse fann June koos oma kalli emaga.

programme.title: Igaviku varavas
programme.desc: Omanaoline eluloofilm Vincent van Goghist (1853- 1890) vaatleb perioodi, mil kunstnik viibis eksiilis Prantsusmaal, Arlesis ja Auvears-sur-Oiseis, kus ta arendas valja oma unikaalsete varvilahendustega maalimisstiili. Katses avada van Goghi siseilma saavad kokku kunstniku võitlus kimbutava vaimuhaigusega, sõprus Paul Gauguiniga ja igavikulised otsingud. Kuldlõvi nominent Veneetsia filmifestivalil. Vincent van Goghi rolli eest palvis Willem Dafoe Oscari ja Kuldgloobuse nominatsiooni parima meespeaosa kategoorias. Lavastaja Oscari nominent Julian Schnabel ("Tuukrikell ja liblikas").

programme.title: Spartalased tulevad!
programme.desc: Kangelaslik Leonidas (Sean Maguire), seljas vaid nahast aluspuksid ja keep, laheb koos oma 13 (jah, tervelt 13!) vapraima sõdalasega vastu nende maad vallutama tulnud Parsia armeele, mille ridadesse kuuluvad muuhulgas Rocky Balboa, Ghost Rider, uks pirakas Transformer ja kuurakas Paris Hilton!

programme.title: Minu spioon
programme.desc: Karmi CIA agendi elu sõltub varakupsest 9-aastasest tudrukust, kelle perekonda ta salaja jalgima saadetakse.

programme.title: Peletiste perekond 2
programme.desc: Mida uuemat on peletiste maailmas? Pulm! Baaba-Jagaa ja tema kallim Renfield, krahv Dracula teener, otsustasid oma tundeid mitte varjata ja... lasta end laulatada! Aga tseremoonia ei jõua alatagi, kui see tuleb katkestada! Kõigi kulaliste silme all roovib armunud noorpaari uleloomulike võimetega peletisekutt Mila Starr. Selgub, et vaike roovija on miljardarist teadlase ainuke tutar ja taidab oma hullu isa antud ulesannet! Sellest lapsukesest tasub eemale hoida - ta on kiire kui tuul ja varustatud selliste abivahenditega, mida kadestaks ka James Bond ise!

programme.title: Kurepoeg Rihhard
programme.desc: Toonekurgede perekonnas ules kasvanud varblasepoiss Rihhard usub, et temagi on toonekurg. Kui saabub aeg lennata talveks lõunamaale, peab kurepere Rihhardile utlema, kes ta tegelikult on. Kuna nii pikka rannakut uks pisike linnuke kaasa teha ei suuda, on nad sunnitud vaikemehe uksi maha jatma. Rihhard aga tahab oma kasuperele tõestada, et on kurg, mis kurg ning asub uksi pikale lennureisile…

programme.title: Koera elu mõte
programme.desc: USA 2017 seiklus komoodia Lavastaja:Lasse Hallstrom, Osades:Dennis Quaid,K. J. Apa,Juliet Rylance Lasse Hallstromi lavastatud "Koera elu mõte" põhineb W. Bruce Cameroni armastatud bestselleril, mis jutustab uhe puhendunud koera (haale andis Josh Gad, "Lumekuninganna ja igavene talv", "Jobs") sudamliku ja ullatava loo.

programme.title: Võimatu missioon
programme.desc: CIA agent Ethan Hunt peab valima sõprade või miljardite inimeste elude vahel. Tehes valiku sõprade heaks, viib ta terve maailma tuumakatastroofi aarele. Nuud vastutab vaid tema oma tegude eest.

programme.title: Kena vaikne kohake
programme.desc: John Krasinski lavastatud õudus-thriller raagib narvekõditava loo Ameerika perekonnast, kes elab idullilises maakohas keset maisipõlde ning kelle ellujaamine sõltub oskusest teha oma toimetusi hiirvaikselt ja sõna lausumata. Vaikeste lastega perekonda piiravad hirmuaratavad võõrolendid, kes kuulevad kõike, kuid ei nae midagi. Niipea kui nad sind kuulevad, langed sa nende saagiks. Olukorra muudab eriti pinevaks asjaolu, et pereema (Emily Blunt) on viimaseid nadalaid beebiootel. Kuidas sunnitada ilma piuksugi tegemata? Kes on need elukad ja mis on nende plaan? Kust nad tulid ja kuidas nende vastu võidelda? Mis on saanud ulejaanud maailmast ja inimkonnast? See pooraselt pingeline jubedik tekitab rohkem kusimusi kui annab vastuseid ning kananahk on vaatajale garanteeritud.

programme.title: Kena vaikne kohake 2
programme.desc: John Krasinski lavastatud õudus-thrilleri "Kena vaikne kohake" teine peatukk jalgib Abbottite perekonna saatust parast esimeses osas aset leidnud traagilisi sundmusi ning heidab pilgu ka võõrolendite saabumise hetke. Parast pereisa Lee (John Krasinski) eneseohverdust, et paasta oma laste elu, on ema Evelyn (Emily Blunt) sunnitud nende senise kodu maha jatma. Pere asub teele, et leida ellujaanuid, kellega võiks jõud uhendada. Kuid peagi selgub, et heli abil jahti pidavad võikad elukad pole ainsad, kes liivaribalt kõrvale astudes su elu kallale kipuvad.

programme.title: Kodachrome - Elu pildid
programme.desc: Plaadikompanii veteran Matt Ryder (Jason Sudeikis) võtab ette pika autosõidu oma vana ja haige isa Benjaminiga (Ed Harris), sihiks viimane labor maailmas, kus ilmutatakse Kodachrome filmi. Benjamin Ryder on nimelt endine tippfotograaf ja tahab teada, mis on jaadvustatud neljale vanale filmirullile, mille ta oma asjade seast leidis. Kahe nageleva mehega sõidab kaasa Beni põetaja Zooey (Elizabeth Olsen). Kõik kolm puuavad hakkama saada poordumatult muutuvas maailmas, uritades oma minevikku selja taha jatta. Huumoriga vurtsitatud draama "Kodachrome _ elu pildid" raagib tegemata valikutest, valusatest-ilusatest malestustest ja andestuse võimalikkusest. Osades Ed Harris ("Westworld", "Apollo 13"), Jason Sudeikis ("Vastikud ulemused"), Elizabeth Olsen ("Tasujad: Igaviku sõda", "Wind River"), Bruce Greenwood ("Kingsman: Kuldne ring", "Geralds Game") ja Dennis Haysbert ("24"). Filmi lavastas Mark Raso ("Copenhagen"), stsenaariumi kirjutas Jonathan Tropper ("This Is Where I Leave You", "Banshee") A.G. Sulzbergeri artikli ainetel.

programme.title: Mina, Tonya
programme.desc: Tonya Harding laks USA ajalukku kui kuulsaim ja skandaalseim iluuisutaja. Tema meisterlikkus leidis pidevalt kinnitust, kuid alatiste skandaalide tõttu oli ta kogu aeg kollases ajakirjanduses.

programme.title: Elliot, kõige vaiksem põhjapõder
programme.desc: Animafilmi tele-esilinastus! Saage tuttavaks tillukese hobusega, kel on hiigelsuur suda ja kes kannab nime Elliot. Üks Jõuluvana põhjapõtradest teatab 21. detsembril ootamatult, et kavatseb pensionile jaada. Talle on vaja leida asendaja ning sellega on kiire! Sudamlik suksu Elliot ja tema parim sõber võtavad suuna Põhjanabale, et võtta osa põhjapõtrade katsetest. Elliot soovib naidata, et just tema on vabaks jaanud ametikohale kõige sobivam... hobune!? Sest suured unistajad unistavadki ju suurelt. Lõbusas ja lustakas jõuluseikluses annavad tegelaskujudele oma haaled teiste seas Tarvo Krall, Erki Aule, Piret Simson, Kati Ong, Karin Aule, Rauno Kaibiainen ja Maarius Parn.

programme.title: Rikkis Ron
programme.desc: Vaimuka animaseikluse "Rikkis Ron" peategelasteks on Barney, ebapopulaarne keskkooliõpilane, ning Ron, tema uhiuus digitaalselt uhendatud, kõndiv ja kõnelev nutiseade, mis peaks olema automaatselt tema parim sõber.

programme.title: Harakapoeg Pingviin
programme.desc: Tõestisundinud lool põhinev film jutustab noorest pereemast nimega Sam Bloom (Naomi Watts), kelle maailm pooratakse pea peale paeval, kui naine õnnetu kukkumise jarel halvatuks jaab. Sami armastav abikaasa Cameron (Andrew Lincoln), tema kolm poega ning ema (Jackie Weaver) naevad tublisti vaeva, et kohaneda uue olukorraga. Pinged koduseinte vahel kasvavad, kuni pere saab ootamatu abilise: vigastatud harakapoja, kellele pannakse nimeks... Pingviin. Linnu saabumine pakub teretulnud vaheldust ning toob kõige suurema muutuse just paljukannatanud Sami jaoks, õpetades teda tasapisi uuesti elama.

programme.title: Baleriin
programme.desc: USA 2017 animatsioon Lavastaja: Eric Summer, Eric Warin Osades: Mirtel Pohla, Mart Muurisepp, Mart Pius, Eduard Toman,Age Oks jt. Felicie on Bretagneist parit noor orb, kel on vaid uks kirg - tantsimine. Ühes parima sõbra Victoriga, kes ihkab suureks leiutajaks saada, kavandab ta poorase põgenemise orbudekodust Valguse linna Pariisi, kus Eiffeli torni alles ehitatakse! Felicie peab nagema vaeva, nagu ei iial varem, end uletama ja õppima vigadest, kui tahab teha teoks oma metsikuima unistuse ja saada Pariisi ooperiteatris priimabaleriiniks.

programme.title: Bill ja Ted
programme.desc: William "Bill" S. Preston Esq. ja Theodore "Ted" Logani jaoks on seekordsel ajarannul kaalul rohkem kui eal varem. Nuudseks keskealised parimad sõbrad asuvad oma rocknrolli saatuse taide viimiseks uuele seiklusele, kui kulaline tulevikust teatab, et vaid nende laul saab paasta maailma. Neid aitavad nende tutred, ajaloolised tegelased ja muusikalegendid, et leida laulu, mis muudaks maailma õigeks ja tooks universumisse harmooniat.

programme.title: Oihhh! Seiklus jatkub
programme.desc: Kui nii edasi laheb, on lõpp kaes! 147 paeva laevas ilma maitsva liha, leiva ja magustoiduta! Ümberringi ainult meri, ei mingit maad silmapiiril, laeval aga 50 tuhat erinevat ja vaga naljast looma, lindu ja kaks sinna juhuslikult sattunud pesalooma. Aga see pole veel kõige hirmsam. Hirmus on see, et varsti saab otsa isegi too jube roheline puder. Ja siis … Siis ei hooli enam keegi reeglist "sina ei pea mitte teist elajat ara sooma"! Kaotanud igasuguse lootuse, laseb kuningas lõvi taevasse tuvi, et see lendaks kõrgele ja otsiks maad … Aga maa leiavad hoopis taiesti juhuslikult laevast valja pudenenud paharetid – grump Liia ja pesaloom Finny! Torm heidab nad erakordselt kaunile saarele.

programme.title: Jargmine ring
programme.desc: Ajaloo, psuhholoogia, muusika ja kehalise õpetaja kontrollivad teaduslikku teooriat, et inimeste kannatusi põhjustab ebapiisavalt alkoholi hulk veres ja et õnnelik olemiseks peab olema pisut svipsis.

programme.title: Mortdecai
programme.desc: Rabeledes vihaste venelaste, Briti salaagentide, oma ilmatu pikkade jalgadega naise ja rahvusvahelise terroristi vahel, peab elurõõmus kunstikaupmees ja poole kohaga suli Charlie Mortdecai, relvaks ainult oma hea valimus ja eriline sarm, minema teisele poole maakera, et tagasi saada varastatud maal, mis kuulujuttude põhjal peidab endas koodi natside kullaga taidetud salajasele pangakontole.

programme.title: La La Land
programme.desc: Algajast naitlejanna Mias ja puhendunud džassmuusik Sebastian naevad vaeva, et saada hakkama linnas, mis on kuulus lootuste purustamise ja sudamete murdmise poolest. programme.title: Suureparased põgenemised koos Morgan Freemaniga

programme.title: Pandikunnid

programme.desc: Harrise vennad lahevad varjatud režiimile. Jarrod ja Brandi on heategevuslikul lainel. Barry leiab koti, mis viib ta suusatama. Darrell avastab suure posti.

programme.desc: Ostjad suunduvad Comptonisse, kus Jarrod saab endale uue huudnime ja leiab midagi, mida ta kunagi kogus. Mike ostab lao, mida Herb ei taha ja Barry uhineb oma vana sõbra Kennyga.

programme.title: William Shatneriga seletamatutes paikades
programme.desc: Kõige suurem mõistatus, millele puudub seni vastus, võib olla meie saatus parast surma. Ehk annavad vihjeid ebaharilikud surmalahedased juhtumid.

programme.title: Pandikunnid
programme.desc: Rick uritab New Yorgis teha tehingu haruldase tehnikavidina ostmiseks. Kas see magus tukk suudab Ricki ahvatleda või loobub ta sellest? Poodi jõuab muuja Stan Lee Funko Popi erivaljaandega. Kas Corey teeb supertehingu?

programme.title: Food Tech
programme.desc: A cheeseburger and a side of fries. Last year, Americans ate over 7 billion of them. And theres an amazing story behind every one. Any idea how they get the sesame seeds to stick to the bun? How do you stuff 20 tomatoes in a ketchup bottle?

programme.title: UFO failid
programme.desc: This documentary series looks into whether there is life beyond earth and whether it has made its way to this planet. Through interviews with scientists, personal sighting and examining suggestive evidence of UFOs the series. By investigating the myths found in cultures and possible sightings of alternative life, the show tries to find evidence for UFO existence.

programme.title: Greatest discoveries
programme.desc: Have a look at the technologies from the past. You will be surprised to find out in what extent ancient knowledge influences modern technology. This series is filmed on location in Italy, Greece, Egypt, England, and other locations of the world where historical events actually happened, and with the help of computer animation ancient machines and mechanisms are reconstructed.

programme.title: Countdown to Apocalypse
programme.desc: Centuries ago the prophet Nostradamus had visions of the end of our modern world. Now, scholars decipher his mysterious predictions and learn of terrible tragedies and catastrophic events that threaten to annihilate global populations.

programme.title: Monsterquest
programme.desc: In different parts of the world there are eyewitnesses who claim they saw various mythical, strange and even scary creatures, from vampires and ghosts to different types of monsters. These individuals tell their stories while a team of experts and scientists use any available evidence to try to find explanations for these unusual sightings.

programme.title: Iidne võimatu
programme.desc: Üks iidne geenius suutis ehitada kahuri, mis tulistas murske auru jõul. Tutvustame teile iidset sõjavae transpordilaeva, mis oli võimsam kui lennukikandja, ning surmavaid kiiri, mis võisid põletada vaenlase laevu.

programme.title: Mankind Decoded
programme.desc: Inspired by the divine, we create monuments to its power (Stonehenge, the Great Pyramid). New challenges create new sciences, and when the Romans mixed volcanic ash with water they created a new super-material: concrete.

programme.title: Mankind Decoded
programme.desc: Using dramatic reconstructions, this fascinating documentary series explores the evolution and advancement of the human race, dissecting the key events and changes that have affected and altered various civilisations. Each episode in this 12-part series focusses on a unique transformation of our ancestors, as they discovered more and more about the planet they inhabit, with expert historians offering explanations to these changes.

programme.title: Battles BC
programme.desc: Step back in time and revisit some of the most brutal battles that took place before Christ. programme.desc: Seven years after the alleged end of the Templars, signs they were rising again appear in Portugal. The team investigate a plan to restart the Templars and explore possibilities that the "Templars 2.0" quietly consolidate power around the world.

programme.title: Monsterquest
programme.desc: In the fall of 1952, witnesses in Flatwoods, West Virginia, reportedly encountered a creature with reptilian skin in a strange craft. As sightings continue, MonsterQuest attempts to uncover the beast that has terrorised this town for sixty years.

programme.title: Lost Worlds
programme.desc: Documentary series that brings back to life lost cities, structures, cultures, and civilisations, transporting viewers back in time and revealing the truth behind some of historys most iconic eras. Using a combination of cutting-edge technology and archaeological research, the team detail what life was like for these places during their peak of their powers, and use visual overlays to compare past and present landscapes.

programme.title: Evolve
programme.desc: Documentary series. Evolve takes an in-depth look at the evolution of some of the planets most iconic animals. Using computer generated imagery and experimental science, the team take you on a journey through history to look at how these species evolved to fit their habitats and surroundings. The show explores the diverse and unique anatomy changes our planets historic species have gone through.

programme.title: Iidsed tulnukad
programme.desc: Muistsete aegade imperaatoritele, kuningatele ja vaaraodele omistati sageli uleloomulikku jõudu, võimeid ja tarkust, alamad pidasid neid sageli jumalateks. Kes need erakordsed juhid tegelikult olid?

programme.title: How the Earth was made
programme.desc: With the help of expert geologists and various scientists, How the Earth Was Made is a remarkable documentary series that examines the powerful forces and events that have shaped our planet. programme.title: Bastille - Reading and Leeds Festival
programme.desc: The Reading and Leeds Festivals are a pair of annual music festivals that take place in Reading and Leeds, England. The events both happen on the bank holiday weekend in August (on Friday, Saturday, Sunday), and share the same bill (occasionally with one or two exceptions). The festivals origins date to the Beaulieu Jazz Festival (1956-1961) which became the National Jazz Festival in 1961 (The National Jazz and Blues Festival in 1963) and settled in Reading in 1971. In 1999 a second leg was added at Leeds. Featuring : Bastille.

programme.title: The Grateful Dead - Classic Albums
programme.sub-title: The Grateful Dead - Classic Albums: Anthem To Beauty
programme.desc: This installment of the Classic Albums series follows the making of two Grateful Dead albums, the fiercely experimental Anthem of the Sun and the understated masterwork American Beauty, which spawned melodic gems like "Sugar Magnolia" and "Ripple." Between the archival scenes and contemporary interviews with band members, the program shows a band making seismic in roads in pop music and five young guys coming to terms with artistry, mortality, and, yes, the pursuit of happiness. There is priceless footage of Neal Cassady driving Ken Keseys bus and of the Dead, surrounded by martini sipping hipsters, on Playboy After Dark. The best scenes involve band members talking about specific songs (you will never hear Phil Leshs "Box of Rain" again without thinking of it as a gift to his dying father) or deconstructing a tune by playing each track separately. Intimate and surprisingly cohesive, Anthem to Beauty is a rare glimpse into how the Deads magic was made.

programme.title: The Moody Blues - Days of Future Passed Live
programme.desc: Celebrating the 50th anniversary of their landmark album, Days of Future Passed, The Moody Blues took to the road to perform the entire LP live. This film, capturing an electric evening at The Sony Centre, Toronto, where the band was joined on stage by a full orchestra for the first time ever, is the definitive performance of this seminal album. This spectacle of a show features stunning visuals and a unique narration performed by Jeremy Irons, transporting the audience and viewer to the psychedelic dream world of their classic record. Including the iconic hits Nights In White Satin and Tuesday Afternoon, this film truly pays homage to five decades of musical mastery. In this impressive yet intimate auditorium, The Moody Blues have never sounded better.

programme.title: Led Zeppelin - Physical Graffiti
programme.sub-title: Led Zeppelin - Physical Graffiti: A Classic Album Under Review
programme.desc: This is a documentary film about the build-up, making, release, and - crucially - music contained on this most revered of albums. With the aid of rare and classic performances, scarce interviews, seldom seen photographs and contributions from those involved in the making of the record - plus the review and critique from a panel of Zeppelin experts - this program finally lifts the lid on what many believe to be Led Zeps very finest offering. With contributions from; the albums engineer, Ron Nevison; former Yardbird, Chris Dreja; Swansong recording artist, Maggie Bell; author of The Rough Guide to Led Zeppelin, Nigel Williamson; Tight But Loose editor, Dave Lewis; Classic Rock Magazines Malcolm Dome; renowned guitar tutor and author, Rikky Rooksby and Robert Plant biographer, Neil Daniels. This is the complete story behind what what Rolling Stone called "their Tommy, Beggars Banquet and Sgt. Pepper rolled into one".

programme.title: The day the Rock Star Died
programme.desc: Michael Jackson American singer, songwriter, dancer and simply the King of Pop. His contributions to music, dance, and publicized personal life made him a global figure in popular culture for over four decades. Jackson made his professional debut in 1964 as a member of The Jackson 5, soon becoming a dominant figure in popular music. His music videos, "Beat It"", "Billie Jean"", and "Thriller"" are credited with breaking racism in the USA and transforming the medium into an art form. Thriller is the best-selling album of all time. Jackson was the most awarded recording artist in the history of popular music. Aspects of Jacksons personal life generated controversy and while preparing for his comeback concert series, This Is It, Jackson died of acute Propofol and Benzodiazepine intoxication on June 25, 2009, after suffering from cardiac arrest. The Los Angeles County Department of Medical Examiner Coroner ruled his death a homicide, and his personal physician, Conrad Murray.
